# Step 1 — Trust-boundary hardening (C1 + C3 + C4 + H1 + H9)
#
# C1: refuse `_net_apply_state` on server-authoritative paths (DS server
#     simulating from input, OR DS-client rendering snapshots). Closes the
#     hole where a peer could RPC `(pos, yaw, pitch)` to its server-side
#     player and override authoritative state.
# C3: server fire handler now enforces ammo / cooldown / reload / loadout.
#     try_fire defers ammo decrement + cooldown set on the server so the
#     handler can validate uniformly across legit input-bit fire AND direct
#     client_fire RPC spam.
# C4: fire-RPC aim is clamped against the shooter's last submitted input
#     yaw/pitch (max delta = PI). Catches teleport-aim cheats.
# H1: `push_remote_input` rejects NaN/Inf, masks bits to known range, caps
#     forward tick-jumps, and validates per-frame aim delta.
# H9: damage feed: capture `prev_hp` before overwriting so the displayed
#     delta is real (was `(max-new)*2`).
#
# Tests: 22/23 pass against run_all.sh. The 1 failure (match_e2e_test) is
# a pre-existing flake — also fails against the backup, unrelated.
#
